    \field{abstract}{%
    This paper presents SPI-DP, a novel first-order optimizer capable of
  optimizing robot programs with respect to both high-level task objectives and
  motion-level constraints. To that end, we introduce DGPMP2-ND, a
  differentiable collision-free motion planner for serial N-DoF kinematics, and
  integrate it into an iterative, gradient-based optimization approach for
  generic, parameterized robot program representations. SPI-DP allows
  first-order optimization of planned trajectories and program parameters with
  respect to objectives such as cycle time or smoothness subject to e.g.
  collision constraints, while enabling humans to understand, modify or even
  certify the optimized programs. We provide a comprehensive evaluation on two
  practical household and industrial applications.%
    }
