    \field{abstract}{%
    This survey explores recent developments in generating digital twins from
  videos. Such digital twins can be used for robotics application, media
  content creation, or design and construction works. We analyze various
  approaches, including 3D Gaussian Splatting, generative in-painting, semantic
  segmentation, and foundation models highlighting their advantages and
  limitations. Additionally, we discuss challenges such as occlusions, lighting
  variations, and scalability, as well as potential future research directions.
